msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To start &libo;, click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Applications</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Office</guimenu> <guimenu>LibreOffice</guimenu></menuchoice>. In "
"the &libo; start center, choose the type of document you want to create."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are multiple methods to directly start one of the &libo; modules:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If any &libo; module is open, you can start any of the other modules by "
"clicking <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>New</guimenu></"
"menuchoice> and then selecting the type of document you want to create."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:206
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also start individual &libo; modules from the menu "
"<guimenu>Applications</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:212
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As an alternative, use the command <command>libreoffice</command> and one of "
"the options <option>--writer</option>, <option>--calc</option>, <option>--"
"impress</option>, <option>--draw</option>, or <option>--base</option> to "
"start the respective module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&libo; has many command line options, especially for allowing document "
"conversions. To learn more about the command line options of &libo;, see "
"<command>libreoffice --help</command> or the man page of &libo; "
"(<command>man libreoffice(1)</command>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:228
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you start working with &libo;, you may be interested in changing some "
"options from the preferences dialog. Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Tools</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Options</guimenu> </menuchoice> to open it. The most "
"important ones are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>&libo;</guimenu><guimenu>User Data</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify your user data such as company, first and last name, street, city, "
"and other useful information. This data has many uses: It is used in the "
"comment functions of Writer and Calc, for authorship information in PDF "
"documents, and for serial letters in Writer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>&libo;</guimenu><guimenu>Fonts</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Map font names to installed fonts. This can be useful if you exchange "
"documents with others and the document you received contains fonts that are "
"not available on your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Load/Save</guimenu><guimenu>General</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

