#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:279
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &libo; User Interface"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user interface of most &libo; is very similar across its modules:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "Menu Bar"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the top of the application, there is the menu bar which gives access to "
"almost all functionality of &libo;. The menu bar can be customized to "
"include more or fewer functions. You can also add and remove menus."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:296
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toolbars"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the toolbars are positioned directly below the menu bar. The "
"toolbars comprise the most used and most important items of the module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To dock a toolbar to any other side of the window, drag them to the right "
"position. To make a toolbar float, drag it into the middle of the window. "
"They can be customized to include more or fewer functions. You can also add "
"and remove toolbars."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Side Bar"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the side bar is positioned at the right side of the &libo; "
"window. On the first start of &libo;, it is only visible as several icons "
"stacked vertically. Clicking one of the icons opens a panel with more "
"elements. Click the icon again to close the panel. Similarly to the "
"toolbars, the side bar comprises the most important functions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To dock the side bar to the left or right side of the window, drag it to the "
"right position. To make the side bar float, drag it into the middle of the "
"window. To hide the side bar, click the vertical arrowhead button on the "
"document-facing side of the side bar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can hide or show side bar panels but cannot customize their "
"functionality."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:334
#, no-c-format
msgid "Statusbar"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The statusbar is displayed at the bottom of the window. It mainly shows "
"information about the document, such as the number of words (in Writer) or "
"the sum of values of selected cells (in Calc). However, it can also be used "
"to change the zoom or language settings. Many elements open additional menus "
"or dialogs on left click, right click, or double click."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information on customizing &libo;, see <xref linkend=\"sec.oo.oview."
"cust\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compatibility with Other Office Applications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:355
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The native file format of &libo; is the OpenDocument format. OpenDocument is "
"an ISO-standardized format for office documents that is based on XML. "
"However, &libo; can also work with documents, spreadsheets, presentations, "
"and databases in many other formats, including Microsoft Office formats. "
"Files in Microsoft Office formats can be opened and saved back normally."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:365
#, no-c-format
msgid "Opening Documents from Other Office Suites"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use &libo; in an environment where you need to share documents with "
"Microsoft Word users, you should have little or no trouble exchanging "
"document files. However, very complex documents can require editing after "
"opening. Complex documents are documents containing, for example, "
"complicated tables, Microsoft Office macros, or unusual fonts, formatting, "
"or graphics objects."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case there should ever be issues with opening documents, try the "
"following strategies:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:381
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text Documents"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider opening text documents in the original application and saving them "
"as RTF or plain text (TXT). However, saving as plain text means that all "
"formatting will be lost."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:391
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spreadsheets"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:392
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider opening spreadsheets in the original application and saving them as "
"Excel files. If this does not work, try the CSV format. However, saving as "
"CSV means that all formatting, cell type definitions, formulas, and macros "
"will be lost."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "Converting Documents to the OpenDocument Format"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&libo; can read, edit, and save documents in several formats. It is not "
"necessary to convert files from those formats to the OpenDocument format "
"used by LibreOffice to use those files. However, if you want to convert the "
"files, you can do so. To convert several documents, such as when first "
"switching to &libo;, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:416
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Wizards</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Document Converter</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:422
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose the file format from which to convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:427
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Next</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify where &libo; should look for templates and documents to convert and "
"in which directory the converted files should be placed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:436
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Documents retrieved from a Windows partition are usually in a subdirectory "
"of <filename>/windows</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:442
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that all other settings are correct, then click <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:448
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review the summary of the actions to perform, then start the conversion by "
"clicking <guimenu>Convert</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The amount of time needed for the conversion depends on the number of files "
"and their complexity. For most documents, conversion does not take long."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:459
#, no-c-format
msgid "When everything is done, close the Wizard."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:467
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sharing Files with Users of Other Office Suites"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&libo; is available for several operating systems. This makes it an "
"excellent tool when a group of users frequently need to share files and do "
"not use the same system on their computers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:473
#, no-c-format
msgid "When sharing documents with others, you have several options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:478
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the recipient needs to be able to edit the file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:480
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the document in the format the other user needs. For example, to save "
"as a Microsoft Word file, click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Save As</guimenu> </menuchoice>, then select the Microsoft Word "
"file type for the version of Word the other user needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:490
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the recipient only needs to read the document"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:492
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Export the document to a PDF file with <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Export as PDF</guimenu> </menuchoice>. PDF files can be read on any "
"platform using a PDF viewer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LibreOffice has a nice functionality that allows adding an OpenDocument into "
"a PDF file. This way, you can share it with anyone with a PDF reader. If the "
"person additionally uses LibO/AOO, they can also edit. File > Export as PDF "
"> Embed OpenDocument File -- sknorr, 2015-09-17"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:506
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sharing a document for editing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:508
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Agree on a common exchange format that works for everyone. TXT and RTF "
"formats, although limited in formatting, can be a good option for text "
"documents."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:516
#, no-c-format
msgid "E-mailing a document as a PDF"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:518
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Send</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>E-mail as PDF</guimenu> </menuchoice>. Your default e-mail program "
"opens with the file attached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:526
#, no-c-format
msgid "E-mailing a document to a Microsoft Word user"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Send</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>E-mail as Microsoft Word</guimenu> </menuchoice>. Your default e-"
"mail program opens with the file attached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:539
#, no-c-format
msgid "Saving Files with a Password"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can save files, no matter in which &libo; format, with a password. "
"Unlike older versions of &libo;, the encryption applied to the document with "
"recent versions of &libo; is very strong. However, this encryption does not "
"protect file names and file sizes of encrypted files. If that is important "
"to you, see the alternate encryption methods described in <xref linkend="
"\"cha.security.cryptofs\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To save a file with a password, select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Save</guimenu> </menuchoice> or <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Save As</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the dialog that opens, activate the check box <guimenu>Save with "
"password</guimenu> at the bottom and click <guimenu>Save</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:566
#, no-c-format
msgid "Type and confirm your password, then click <guimenu>OK</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:571
#, no-c-format
msgid "The next time you open the file, you will be prompted for the password."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:575
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the password, do either of the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:580
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Overwrite the same file by selecting <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenu>Save As</guimenu></menuchoice>. Make sure <guimenu>Save "
"with Password</guimenu> is deactivated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Properties</guimenu> </"
"menuchoice> and click <guimenu>Change Password</guimenu> to access the "
"password dialog."
msgstr ""

